Hall, Respondent, v. Dennerlein, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and-Comity, General Term. March 9, 1891.) Appeal from special term.

Argued before Daly, C. J., and Pryor, J.

H. C. Henderson, for appellant. Thos. S. Bassford, for respondent.

No opinion. Appeal dismissed, with $10 costs. See 14 N. Y. Supp. 796 11 N. Y. Supp. 952, 954, mems.
